President Muhammadu Buhari has postponed his earlier scheduled trip to the United Kingdom for medical follow-up.
This disclosure is contained in a short statement issued by the Special Adviser to the President on Media and Publicity, Femi Adesina, on Friday, June 25, 2021.
Adesina said that a new date will be announced for the trip which was earlier scheduled for Friday, June 25, 2021.
“The medical follow-up visit of President Muhammadu Buhari to the United Kingdom earlier scheduled for today, Friday, June 25, 2021, has been postponed. A new date will be announced in due course,’’ the statement read.

